```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['miles'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['miles'], data['gas'])
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.ylabel('Gas Used (gallons)')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('How does the amount of gas used vary with miles driven?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['miles'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.title('What is the trend in miles driven over the years?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
```
```python
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = data.boxplot(column='miles', by='side')
    ax.set_title('')
    plt.title('How does the side of the road affect miles driven?', wrap=True)
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Side of the Road')
    plt.ylabel('Miles Driven')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
